  "title": "Manager",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities</p><ul><li>Drive APAC business growth through design: Ensure design contributes directly to business development,\ndifferentiation, and deal success in the APAC region.</li><li>Align HQ design strategy with regional execution: Translate HQ's design vision, standards, and priorities into\nmarket-relevant APAC initiatives</li><li>Position design as a strategic function: Establish design as a trusted partner to APAC BUs and R&D leadership</li><li>Lead APAC design strategy and priorities: Define focus areas and ensure early design involvement in key business, PoC, and R&D initiatives.</li><li>Integrate business, R&D, and design: Act as the primary design interface connecting APAC BUs, research\norganizations, and HQs. </li><li>Ensure value delivery and quality: Oversee design outcomes to ensure market relevance, usability, and\nconsistency with NEC standards. </li><li>Build and scale the APAC design organization: Establish clear roles, engagement models, and governance within a matrix organization.</li><li>Develop design talent and capabilities: Recruit, coach, and grow multicultural design talent with strong\nbusiness and technology literacy.</li><li>Embed a design-led culture: Promote customer-centric, collaborative, and evidence-based ways of\nworking across the region.</li></ul><p>Requirements</p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Product design, or related field.</li><li>More than 5 years of Product design experience in a multi-national IT company.</li><li>Project management skill is a must.</li><li>Knowledge and Practice of Visual Identity and Corporate Identity</li><li>Experience in working with a diverse, geographically remote team.</li><li>Effective influencing, organizational and problem-solving skills.</li><li>Excellent interpersonal, negotiation, communication skills and ability to interact with all levels.</li><li>Strong presentation skills and ability to write professionally in both English and Japanese.</li><li>Proficiency in the Japanese language (JLPT N1) to liaise with NEC’s headquarters in Japan.</li></ul>",
